# API Contracts and Resilience

- Validate all request payloads, params, and query shapes strictly.
- Keep response schemas stable; preserve backward compatibility.
- Version contract changes and document migration path.
- Log errors with actionable context (endpoint, input class, correlation id).
- Apply retries/timeouts/circuit-breaker patterns for external dependencies.
- Protect uptime with health checks and graceful degradation behavior.
